text: Deep Web is a 2015 documentary film directed by Alex Winter, chronicling events surrounding Silk Road, bitcoin and politics of the dark web. Covering the trial of Ross Ulbricht, the documentary features interviews with Wired writer Andy Greenberg and developer Amir Taaki. Deep Web features narration from actor Keanu Reeves. The film premiered at the 2015 South By Southwest film festival, and aired on the Epix network on May 31, 2015. ==See also== * Darknet market ==References== ==External links== * * * Category:2015 documentary films Category:2015 films Category:American films Category:American documentary films Category:Bitcoin Category:Dark web Category:Darknet markets Category:Documentary films about the Internet Category:Documentary films about crime in the United States Category:English- language films Category:Films directed by Alex Winter Category:2010s documentary film stubs
